.:: Zebra puzzle ::.
5 different games are played: mah-jongg, billiard, go, snooker, chess
The people use 5 different means of transport: airplane, van, helicopter, jet-ski, taxi
The people grow 5 different varities of flowers: rose, dahlia, begonia, tulip, bellflower
City: venice, colone, prague, san-francisco, marseilles
The people have 5 different jobs:  engineer, coach, designer, project-manager, mechanic

1. the person driving the airplane is the person playing mah-jongg
2. the person driving the van is the engineer
3. the person traveling to venice is the person playing billiard
4. the person driving the helicopter is the person traveling to colone
5. the person playing billiard is to the right of the person playing go
6. the person who growsrose is the mechanic
7. the person who growsdahlia is the person playing snooker
8. the person traveling to prague is in the middle
9. the person driving the jet-ski is on the far left
10. the person who growsbegonia is on the left or right of the coach
11. the person who growsdahlia is to the left or right of the project-manager
12. the person who growstulip is the person traveling to san-francisco
13. the person driving the taxi is the person who growsbellflower
14. the person driving the jet-ski is to the left or right of the person playing chess

.:: Answer ::.
|		|       1	|	2	|	3 	|	4	|	5	|
| Transport	|   jet-ski	|    helicopter	|     airplane	|    van	|    taxi	|
| Game		|    snooker	|      chess	|      mah-jongg	|     go	|     billiard	|
| City	|     marseilles	|      colone	|      prague	| san-francisco	|     venice	|
| Flower		|     dahlia	| chesterfield	|    olg-gold	| tulip	|   parliament	|
| Job		|     coach	|     project-manager	|     mechanic	|     engineer	|     designer	|
